Citation.sTitle: Solubilities of cinnamic acid, phenoxyacetic acid and 4-methoxyphenylacetic acid in supercritical carbon dioxide
Citation.sAbstract: The solid solubilities of cinnamic acid, phenoxyacetic acid and 4-methoxyphenylacetic acid in supercritical carbon dioxide were measured using a semi-flow apparatus. The experiments were taken at 308.2, 318.2 and 328.2 K. The pressure range was from 11 to 24MPa. These data were confirmed as equilibrium solid solubilities based on a plug flow mass transfer model. The solid solubilities were further correlated using the equations of state or semi-empirical models. The correlation results are satisfactory with optimally fitted binary interaction parameters in the Peng Robinson equation of state.
